            "body": "> I know we've seen at least two bug reports for this and the Numpy bindings that we've directed to you.\r\n\r\nRight, it seems a bit like it might have changed at some point?  If this was a while ago, I honestly don't care too much.  In general I prefer the use of `index` and using `int(value)` explicitly when it is not desired.\r\n\r\nTBH, I would be happy if such a switch is possible, also without the special handling  (because it is questionable also, so opting in to both at once seems perfectly fine).",
